Gene Set Enrichment Analysis (RT vs CLL)

Ramon Massoni-Badosa

Compiled: enero 11, 2022

1 Introduction

Here we will perform a gene set enrichment analysis (GSEA) using clusterprofiler with the differentially expressed genes we obtained previously.

2 Pre-processing

2.1 Load packages

library(Seurat)
library(clusterProfiler)
library(org.Hs.eg.db)
library(ggrepel)
library(ggforce)
library(tidyverse)

2.2 Define parameters

# Paths
path_to_obj <- here::here("results/R_objects/Penter2021/3.seurat_obj_clustered_Penter2021.rds")
path_to_deg <- here::here("results/R_objects/Penter2021/dea_RT_vs_CLL_Penter2021.rds")
path_to_save_rds <- here::here("results/R_objects/Penter2021/gsea_RT_vs_CLL_Penter2021.rds")
path_to_save_xlsx <- here::here("results/tables/Penter2021/gsea_RT_vs_CLL_Penter2021.xlsx")


# Colors
color_palette <- c("black", "gray", "red", "yellow", "violet", "green4",
                   "blue", "mediumorchid2", "coral2", "blueviolet",
                   "indianred4", "deepskyblue1", "dimgray", "deeppink1",
                   "green", "lightgray", "hotpink1")
cols_rt <- c("#dcdddc", "#cd8899")


# Source functions
source(here::here("bin/utils.R"))


# Thresholds
alpha <- 0.05
GO_max_total_genes <- 250
GO_min_enriched_genes <- 3
GO_p_adj_threshold <- 0.01
GO_min_odds_ratio <- 2.5
max_gs_size <- 250
min_gs_size <- 10
simplify_cutoff <- 0.75

2.3 Load data

# Load Seurat object
seurat <- readRDS(path_to_obj)


# Plot
DimPlot(seurat, group.by = "disease_state", cols = cols_rt) +
  theme(plot.title = element_blank())

seurat$donor_id <- str_remove(seurat$sample_id, "_.*$")
DimPlot(seurat, group.by = "donor_id", cols = color_palette) +
  theme(plot.title = element_blank())

DimPlot(seurat, group.by = "tissue") +
  theme(plot.title = element_blank())

# Load DEG
dea <- readRDS(path_to_deg)

3 GSEA

set.seed(1234)
gene_list <- dea$avg_log2FC
names(gene_list) <- dea$gene
gsea_results <- gseGO(
  gene_list,
  ont = "BP",
  OrgDb = org.Hs.eg.db,
  keyType = "SYMBOL",
  minGSSize = min_gs_size,
  maxGSSize = max_gs_size,
  seed = TRUE
)
gsea_results <- clusterProfiler::simplify(
  gsea_results,
  cutoff = simplify_cutoff
)
gsea_sorted <- gsea_results@result %>%
  dplyr::filter(p.adjust < alpha) %>%
  dplyr::arrange(desc(NES))
DT::datatable(gsea_sorted, options = list(scrollX = TRUE))
# Plot
(dot_plot_gsea <- clusterProfiler::dotplot(
  gsea_results,
  x = "NES",
  showCategory = 40,
  color = "p.adjust"
) +
  theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 11)))

4 Calculate OXPHOS and BCR signatures

# GSEA plots
selected_terms <- c("GO:0006119", "GO:0050853")
selected_titles <- c(
  "oxidative phosphorylation",
  "B cell receptor signaling pathway"
)
gsea_plots <- purrr::map2(selected_terms, selected_titles, function(x, title) {
  p <- gseaplot(gsea_results, geneSetID = x, by = "runningScore", title = title)
  p
})
gsea_plots
## [[1]]

## 
## [[2]]

# Calculate signatures. Since the gene symbols of mitochondrial genes in Seurat
# object start with "MT-", we will add this prefix in the gene symbols of the
# OXPHOS set.
gene_sets <- gsea_results@geneSets
signatures <- list(
  oxphos = gene_sets$`GO:0006119`,
  bcr_signaling = gene_sets$`GO:0050853`
)
mt_genes <- rownames(seurat) %>%
  str_subset("^MT-") %>%
  str_remove("^MT-")
signatures$oxphos[signatures$oxphos %in% mt_genes] <- str_c(
  "MT-",
  signatures$oxphos[signatures$oxphos %in% mt_genes],
  sep = ""
)
seurat <- AddModuleScore(
  seurat,
  features = signatures,
  name = names(signatures)
)


# Plot
selected_sign <- c("oxphos1", "bcr_signaling2")
selected_titles2 <- c("OXPHOS Score", "BCR Signaling Score")
umaps_sign <- purrr::map2(selected_sign, selected_titles2, \(x, y) {
  p <- FeaturePlot(seurat, x) +
    scale_color_viridis_c(option = "magma") +
    ggtitle(y)
  p
})
umaps_sign

vln_rt_vs_cll <-  purrr::map2(selected_sign, selected_titles2, \(x, y) {
  p <- VlnPlot(
    seurat,
    x,
    group.by = "disease_state",
    cols = cols_rt,
    pt.size = 0
  ) +
    ylab(y) +
    theme(
      plot.title = element_blank(),
      legend.position = "none",
      axis.title.x = element_blank(),
      axis.title.y = element_text(size = 11),
      axis.text = element_text(size = 10)
    )
  p
})
vln_rt_vs_cll
## [[1]]

## 
## [[2]]

df <- seurat@meta.data
vln_rt_vs_cll2 <-  purrr::map2(selected_sign, selected_titles2, \(x, y) {
  p <- df %>%
    ggplot(aes_string("sample_id", x, fill = "disease_state")) +
      geom_violin() +
      scale_fill_manual(values = cols_rt) +
      ylab(y) +
      theme_classic() +
      theme(
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, vjust = 1),
        legend.title = element_blank(),
        legend.position = "top"
      )
  p
})
